PART 2 — DESIGN SYSTEM & VISUAL DESIGN STANDARDS
18. Design System Overview
18.1 Purpose
The Design System provides a unified visual language for the AI Threat Hunting & Threat Intelligence Agent. It ensures consistency, scalability, accessibility, and maintainability across all user interfaces by defining standardized colors, typography, spacing, components, layouts, and interaction behaviors.
The system is designed specifically for cybersecurity professionals who work with large amounts of data and require interfaces that emphasize clarity, efficiency, and rapid decision-making.

Objectives
The Design System aims to:
Ensure visual consistency
Improve usability
Accelerate frontend development
Support responsive layouts
Simplify component reuse
Maintain accessibility compliance
Provide a cohesive user experience
