PART 4 — DASHBOARD & THREAT INTELLIGENCE UI DESIGN
78. Dashboard Module Overview
78.1 Purpose
The Dashboard serves as the primary operational workspace for Security Operations Center (SOC) analysts, threat researchers, security administrators, and executives. It consolidates cybersecurity intelligence into a single interface, providing real-time visibility into the organization's security posture.
The dashboard is designed to reduce cognitive load while enabling rapid identification, investigation, and response to cyber threats.

Objectives
The dashboard enables users to:
Monitor live threats
View security posture
Investigate vulnerabilities
Track malware campaigns
Monitor phishing attacks
Analyze Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)
Review AI-generated insights
Generate reports
Monitor notifications
79. Dashboard Design Philosophy
The dashboard follows these principles:
Present critical information first
Reduce unnecessary visual clutter
Use meaningful colors
Prioritize actionable data
Maintain consistent layouts
Minimize scrolling
Enable rapid navigation
