145. Accessibility Overview
The platform targets WCAG 2.2 AA compliance to ensure usability for all users.
Accessibility is integrated into every component rather than treated as an afterthought.

146. Accessibility Features
Supported features include:
Keyboard Navigation
Screen Reader Support
High Contrast Mode
Visible Focus Indicators
Semantic HTML
Accessible Forms
Accessible Charts
Skip Navigation Links
Adjustable Text Size
147. Keyboard Navigation
Users can navigate the application using only the keyboard.
Supported shortcuts include:

Shortcut	Action
Tab	Next Element
Shift + Tab	Previous Element
Enter	Activate
Esc	Close Modal
Arrow Keys	Navigate Lists
Ctrl + K	Global Search
Ctrl + /	Open AI Assistant
148. Screen Reader Support
The interface uses:
ARIA Labels
Landmark Roles
Descriptive Button Labels
Accessible Tables
Form Descriptions
All interactive elements include meaningful labels.
149. Color Contrast Standards
Minimum contrast ratios:
Content	Contrast Ratio
Normal Text	4.5 : 1
Large Text	3 : 1
Icons	3 : 1
UI Components	3 : 1
Severity colors are selected to remain distinguishable in both light and dark themes.
