155. Security UX Guidelines
The interface communicates security-related information clearly.
Authentication
Session expiration warnings
Secure password indicators
Login attempt feedback
Sensitive Actions
Confirmation dialogs are required before:
Deleting users
Removing threat feeds
Changing AI configuration
Resetting passwords
Deleting reports
Audit Awareness
Users are informed when administrative actions are logged for auditing purposes.
156. Performance & Usability Standards
Target performance metrics:
Metric	Target
First Contentful Paint	< 1.8 s
Largest Contentful Paint	< 2.5 s
Time to Interactive	< 3 s
Initial Bundle Size	< 500 KB (gzipped)
Dashboard Refresh	< 2 s
Usability Principles
Minimize clicks for common tasks
Keep navigation consistent
Preserve user context
Display meaningful feedback
Avoid unnecessary modal dialogs
